{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Node3D"]]},"kind":"symbol","identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Node3D\/lookAt(target:up:useModelFront:)","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"sections":[],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Rotates the node so that the local forward axis (-Z, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Vector3.FORWARD"},{"text":") points toward the ","type":"text"},{"code":"target","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" position.","type":"text"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"final","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"lookAt","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"target","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Vector3","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Vector3","preciseIdentifier":"s:10SwiftGodot7Vector3V"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"text":"up","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:10SwiftGodot7Vector3V","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Vector3","text":"Vector3","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":" = Vector3 (x: 0, y: 1, z: 0), "},{"text":"useModelFront","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","text":"Bool"},{"text":" = false)","kind":"text"}],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The local up axis (+Y) points as close to the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"up"},{"text":" vector as possible while staying perpendicular to the local forward axis. The resulting transform is orthogonal, and the scale is preserved. Non-uniform scaling may not work correctly.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"target"},{"type":"text","text":" position cannot be the same as the node’s position, the "},{"code":"up","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" vector cannot be zero, and the direction from the node’s position to the "},{"code":"target","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" vector cannot be parallel to the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"up"},{"type":"text","text":" vector."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Operations take place in global space, which means that the node must be in the scene tree.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If "},{"code":"useModelFront","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"type":"text","text":", the +Z axis (asset front) is treated as forward (implies +X is left) and points toward the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"target"},{"type":"text","text":" position. By default, the -Z axis (camera forward) is treated as forward (implies +X is right)."}]}],"kind":"content"}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/node3d\/lookat(target:up:usemodelfront:)"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"metadata":{"externalID":"s:10SwiftGodot6Node3DC6lookAt6target2up13useModelFrontyAA7Vector3V_AISbtF","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"lookAt"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"target"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Vector3","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:10SwiftGodot7Vector3V"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"text":"up","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:10SwiftGodot7Vector3V","text":"Vector3","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"text":"useModelFront","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":